replyContent: Hello Andrei, the latest version of the game fixed this bug. I also emailed you with a workaround if it was still an issue. Would you mind changing your review if the issue is now resolved? Kind Regards, Josh @ Superswatch

content: Great game but I have noticed a bug. The Indy car championship after I won one of them and start a new one, 3 cars carry over their points totals from the previous championship. This has happened for two of them in a row. They usually start around 2,100 after the first race which literally makes it impossible to win the championship even if you win every race because you get 185 points to win. You can only accumulate 2,200 points if you win every race.
I love it to the max only thing is can you make it as the chase format like elimination format of tight now

Long car rides? Pft, no problem just start a championship series and Fight to win and fight through a hungry pack of 42 other racers. It also has 3 types of racing series' you have stock car, trucks and IndyCar. There is also fun challenges for you to try but be warned as they are only for the best of the best! So in conclusion if you like action packed tight racing then try out Draftmaster as you won't be disappointed. Hope this helps you get an idea of this game!
Fantastic game with great mechanics that make sense and feel real. Don't normally like retro looking games but it just works with this game. As a racing fan, love it, love it, love it!
PLEASE ADD MORE STOCK CARS, I REALLY WANT THE BURGER KING CAR, AHHHHHH
Terrific
Love the pixel art gameplay <3<3<3
love the game. only complaint is championship scoring.

There should be a Chase format like real nascar that would make it a lot more fun and interesting, a paint booth for a custom car would be great, pit stops and wrecks should be able to happen, and instead of the camera rotating the cars should actually turn and go through a turn and you should have a race shop that shows all the trophies you won from each track and, cautions. If these features were added to the game it would be a way more popular game, these minor things can make it so much better.

Excellent Little Time Waster.

Free version was great, Pro version is better. Would love to see championships for trucks and indycar. Push to pass on indycars would be awesome. Just an amazing, simple to learn, tons of fun, high octane racing game. Well done, sir! P.s. for some reason I did not get the starting credits but the doubler is working.

One of the best mobile games out there I usually hate mobile games because they are usually pay to win or have a timer on it but this you can play for hours supper fun for nascar fans and non nascar fans. Great game very enjoyable.

This IS the best game. Greatest of all time. PERIOD. The only reason i upgraded to the pro version was for the 28 car icon instead of the 48, well played developer, well played... I think the the simplicity of it is what is great, you arent building up attributes or earning points to buy better equipment. You just hop in and race. There is only one way to truely make it even better and that is If there was a version for PS4 where you could race online with friends. But never the less, Two BIG thumbs up!

Had free version and loved it. Bought Pro version for the extra goodies. ;-) Play it ALL the time. Just waiting for more paint schemes, specifically the other Days Of Thunder cars... ;-) What about having Championship mode for the trucks and indy cars too?? GREAT game. LOVE the Atari feel / look to it.

Needs a career mode where you start out with a minor sponsor and a slow car. Work your way up to better sponsors and better equipment. Also could use a car editor like in the old Papyrus NASCAR games where you could do the paint schemes on your car.
Basic fun

Loved the free game, so I bought the Pro version.  I love the challenges and editors. Possible New Features: 1)Championships with all cars 2)Fuel consumption:drafting uses less fuel, also enables a boost when not in a draft or leading.  Running "out" means slightly lower speed. 3)Damage: aggressive bump drafting leads to cumulative damage.  After a point, it could slow your car, or cost you some of your winnings. 4)Being able to import carsets (I'm willing to contribute gfx). 5)Individual car performance to reduce randomness 6)More championships to unlock for in-game cash (could go with the carset idea)  Unlock the championship with cash, then buy cars within that set to race with. Would pay $2 more dollars for these features!
I bought the Pro Version! This is a great no turbo, no NOS, & no turtle shell game!!!! Very excited to play more and experiment with the physics portion!
Finally a pro version! This is my favorite game to every come to the play store. Hopefully many more good things to come! Keep up the good work Josh!
Thank you for purchasing Draftmaster Pro! Hope you enjoy the game and get plenty of extra enjoyment from all of the Pro features!
